"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The use of `apply` with a lambda function on a groupby object is not returning a Series of the same length as the original DataFrame, which can lead to misalignment of indices when assigning to `df['z']`. This will raise a ValueError due to shape mismatch.\", \"patch\": \"9c9\\n< df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1))).reset_index(drop=True)\\n---\\n> df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1))).explode().reset_index(drop=True)\"}"